          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Improving Recovery and Reunifying Families Act </strong></p> <p>This bill provides resources for the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS)&nbsp;to evaluate a family recovery and reunification program and determine whether the program should be replicated. HHS must use a model that is designed to help reunify&nbsp;families and protect children by working with parents or guardians with a substance use disorder who have temporarily lost custody of their children.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDate>2018-05-22</actionDate>
        </item>
